# Personal To-Do Manager

Manages your personal daily tasks in the `to_do's/` folder.

**Note:** For tracking **product initiatives** (phases, generated documents), use `pm-progress.json` (see `.cursor/rules/progress-tracker.mdc`). This module is for **personal day-to-day tasks**.

---

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `tasks.md` | Today's tasks with checkboxes |
| `backlog.md` | Future tasks / P3 |
| `progress-log.md` | Cumulative history from morning briefings |

---

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| "Show my to-do's" | Display contents of tasks.md |
| "Add to-do: [description]" | Add checkbox to tasks.md |
| "Complete to-do [title]" | Mark as [x] and move to Completed |
| "Today's to-do's" | List P1 and P2 from tasks.md |
| "Morning briefing" | Update tasks.md AND progress-log.md |

## Natural Language Triggers

Recognize natural variants for task actions:

| Intent | Trigger Phrases | Action |
|--------|----------------|--------|
| Add task | "remind me to X", "need to do X", "add task X", "to-do: X" | Add to tasks.md, infer priority |
| Complete task | "finished X", "done with X", "completed X" | Mark [x], move to Completed |
| Show tasks | "what do I have", "my to-do's", "what's pending" | List P1 and P2 from tasks.md |

Rules:
- Infer priority from context: if it mentions blocker/urgent -> P1; if follow-up -> P2
- If ambiguous, ask: "P1 (urgent) or P2 (important)?"
- Accept any natural phrasing — don't require exact format

---

## Task IDs

Every task created from meeting notes, commitments, or cross-file workflows **must** receive a stable ID for cross-file sync.

**Format:** `^pm-YYYYMMDD-NNN` (e.g., `^pm-20260323-001`)

- `YYYYMMDD` = date the task was created
- `NNN` = sequential counter for that day (001, 002, ...)
- The ID is appended at the end of the task text in parentheses

**Example:**
```markdown
- [ ] Follow up with Maiki on Q2 roadmap alignment (^pm-20260323-001)
```

**Cross-file sync rules:**
- When a task with an ID is **completed**, search for the same ID across `to_do's/`, `documents/`, and `context/people/` and mark it complete everywhere
- When completing, add timestamp: `- [x] Task text (^pm-20260323-001) ✅2026-03-23`
- Tasks created from meeting notes get IDs assigned at creation time
- Tasks created from commitments share the same ID in `commitments.md`
- Tasks added manually via "add task" do NOT require IDs (only cross-file tasks need them)

**When to assign IDs:**
- Meeting notes action items (meeting-notes skill)
- Commitments extracted from meetings
- Tasks that appear in multiple files (person pages, meeting notes, tasks.md)
- Do NOT add IDs to quick personal tasks that only live in tasks.md

